cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with cryptography and communication protocols, which are typically classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of finite vector spaces and geometric constructions suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG), while the problem of communicating without revealing information about specific cards relates to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes a new protocol for solving the generalized Russian cards problem, which could be seen as a contribution to the field of computational complexity (cs.CC).
